$ Shell command: lspci
@ lspci

`lspci` lists all connected → hardware/PCI devices regardless whether the respective driver is installed or not.

{ Showing kernel drivers etc.

  `lspci -k` shows the kernel driver that is being used to handle the respective PCI device.

}

